		"description": "<div class=\"field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field--item\">\n<p>Even a well-told lie of being harmless only works if you&rsquo;re really believing it when you tell it&mdash;and in the midst of a pitched fight it&rsquo;s easy to muster some real feeling to briefly fool a foe.</p>\n<p>When a creature makes an attack against you, you can use your reaction to make a Deception or nonmusical Performance check with <span class=\"freelinking-link\">disadvantage</span> , opposed by its Insight check. On a success, the creature is briefly perplexed and targets a different creature with the attack instead.</p>\n</div>",
